from what i can see dolfie dreams are resin cast as well. They warn you of the usage of acetone. Which is an good indicator these are resin cast.
You can use acetone to clean up faces. But you need to wash them of with water immediatly after. Since the acetone makes the material go brittle and slimy. posts.name: seuss
posts.com:
Have you tried to bully a wave? Punch at it? Stupid! Did you know human beings spend most of their lives doing something different? Every minute of every day a human being (organism) is doing something different. They are never doing the same thing twice. There is always some idiosyncrasy to a repetition. The few people who complete the same task over and over again are called students, and the even fewer people who have mastered the art of repetition are called teachers. If seuss had to guess, there is about a one in a million chance that this time you and I have posted on [s4s] together is exactly the same as the last one.

The reason people love minutiae of differences is kind of cathartic. Like a religious reason. Imagine the world is made up of atoms and small little dots, and every time you do something, those dots rearrange in a specific way. The Japanese call it... Kintsugi. Restoration and replication is a kind of ideology, it doesn't excuse interpretation or nuance.

>Have you ever tried to bully a wave? Punch it? Kick it? Pinch it? Hit it? Beat it to death with a stick? Stupid. —Ruth Ozeki, A Tale for the Time Being

>In my sister’s story, / God can’t find us in any of / His coat pockets, / not in the empty, and not in the filled. / We’re in none of His hands, the kind or the terrible; / none of His shoes, the giant or the minute. / And neither are we hiding inside the apples, / neither in the perfect nor the ruined. / Not in the first mouthful, and not in the last. —Li-Young Lee, The Shortcut Home

Are you a romantic? Do you think about love under a lamp-lit dinner? Or maybe a skyline filled with lights, during a dusky summer's evening. Is love something you consider only when mystery is involved? And if there is a mystery, are you emotionally attached to that rapacious feeling of excitement that unravels it? If your pre-amp has an out, it may have a "direct monitor" feature which would allow you to hear. Otherwise I think you would need to go into your OS sound settings and "Listen to this device" to make the sound come out of your speakers, or headphones.
